{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χλαῖνα</b>, ης, ἡ, <br /> <b>upper-garment, cloak, wrapper,</b> worn loose over the χιτών, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (see. below), 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 9.3, 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica “Papyrus fragments” in E. Diehl, 22.9, etc.: in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus worn only by men, ἀνεμοσκεπής, ἀλεξάνεμος, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.224, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.529 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πυκνὴ καὶ μεγάλη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 520; οὔλη 4.50, +others; ἀμφὶ δ᾽ ἄρα χλαῖναν περονήσατο φοινικόεσσαν διπλῆν ἐκταδίην 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.133; ἀπ᾽ ὤμοιϊν χ. θέτο 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.118; βῆ δὲ θέειν, ἀπὸ δὲ χ. βάλε 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.183, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.500 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; given as a prize, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.91; as ransom, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.230; αἱ Πελληνικαὶ χ. ἃς καὶ ἆθλα ἐτίθεσαν ἐν τοῖς ἀγῶσι 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 8.7.5 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also used as a <b>blanket</b> or <b>covering</b> in sleep, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.299, 20.4; δέμνια καὶ χλαῖναι καὶ ῥήγεα 11.189; χλαῖναι καὶ ῥήγεα.. ἐνεύδειν 3.349 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of husband and wife, μίμνομεν μιᾶς ὑπὸ χλαίνης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 540, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 603.4, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 18.19, “Anthologia Graeca” 5.164 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus), 168 (1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus): _metaphorically_, χθονὸς χλαῖνα,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] i. e. earth thrown over a body <b>like a cloak</b> or <b>blanket,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 872: porv., ᾗ μήτε χ. μήτε σισύρα συμφέρει\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] content neither with <b>cloak</b> nor rug, i.e. never satisfied, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1459 (the σισύρα\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] being coarser,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare χλαῖναν μαλακήν, σισύραν [prev. author] “V.” 738 (_anapaest meter_)); but also χ. δέ σοι λαβὼν παχεῖαν ἐπιβαλῶ Λακωνικήν 5th c.BC: Theopompus Comicus 10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. πωλεῖν, when spring comes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 715 (_anapaest meter_), compare χλαῖνα· χλανίς, ἢ ἱμάτιον χειμερινόν, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus: proverbial, ἐν τῷ θέρει τὴν χ. κατατρίβων,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] of reckless improvidence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Metrodorus Epigrammaticus “fragment” 55: τράγου χ. μελέα,\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>] of a goatskin <b>cloak,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 80 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9735","accentedUnicode":"χλαῖνα","shortDef":"a goat's hair coat","mediumDef":"a goat's hair coat","stepGloss":"a goat's hair coat","stepTransliteration":"chlaina","_step_Type":"word"}]}